package.json : the main configuration file  of the project.
               Lists all the dependencies your project needs (like React, Vite).
               Stores project metadata: name, version, scripts, license, etc.
               Lets you run commands: e.g., npm start, npm run build
package-lock.json : Automatically generated file by npm.
                    Records exact versions of all installed packages, including nested dependencies.
                    Ensures everyone who installs the  project gets exactly the same versions.
                    Helps prevent bugs caused by different versions of the same library.
                    it locks the version 
                    

(in simple words
                    package.json → Your shopping list (what you want to buy) 
                    package-lock.json → The exact items you bought with brand and version 
Tree Shaking:Removes unused code from production bundle,Reduces final bundle size → faster websites/apps.
Development Machine:where you write and test code
Production Machine :Environment where the final app is deployed for users.
